parameters:
\n<Guild Master>What's with this cat brat. Hey! Who's the guardian of these
kids? Stray cats, huh?! Kick them out!

\n<Louiesham>We didn't wander in by mistake. This is the Adventurer's
Guild, right? I believe everyone has the right to enter.

\n<Guild Master>Huh? No way. Our guild clearly states at the entrance that
those who cover their poop with sand are not welcome.

\n<Adventurer A>Hahaha! Don't be too hard on them! They seem to have
something to say. At least listen to their story, Master!

\n<Wanzworth>I'm looking for my sister. A beastman, a very strong
adventurer. Do you know anything?

\n<Guild Master>Even if I did know, you think I'd tell you for free? Don't
they teach you in school these days that information has
value?
\n<Louiesham>Then, how about this...
Paid 1000G...
\n<Guild Master>Hmm, a cat adventurer, eh? Don't know 'em.
\n<Wanzworth>What's that about! Then give me back my money!

\n<Guild Master>You've just obtained the information that "I don't know
anything." Got it? Now get out, cat brat.

\n<Adventurer B>Hey, wait a sec. You've got quite a cute face there, don't
ya Despite the baby face, you've got curves in all the
right places Uhihi

\n<Wanzworth>Hey! Don't touch me! Ew! You reek of alcohol! Don't come any
closer!

\n<Adventurer B>Come on, don't be like that. Uncle will take good care of
you Kukuku
Please select the protagonist.
Help (Male Protagonist)
Flip Out (Female Protagonist)
\n<Adventurer B>Gubeh!!!
MP_SET_MOVIE 1
MP_SET_MOVIE 1
MP_SET_LOOP 20 on

\n<Wanzworth>Oh, sorry. I might have gone too far. You're not dead, are
you? Did it hurt? But it's your fault, you know.

\n<Louiesham>So, it would be in everyone's best interest not to
underestimate us too much...

\n<Louiesham>You really shouldn't underestimate us. We've been practicing
quite a bit, and it would be bad if we accidentally killed
someone because we couldn't control it well.

\n<Wanzworth>That was a bit too much. Did you really have control? Are
you okay, mister?
\n<Adventurer A>Wahahahahaha! You guys are the best!!
\n<Adventurer C>Yaaay Kitty cats So strong So cute
\n<Adventurer D>...! There are hands in the air...
\n<Adventurer E>This is quite something! Extraordinary magical power...

\n<Guild Master>You're good! Hahahaha! Sorry for mocking you! Forgive my
rudeness.
\n<Guild Master>You said you were looking for an adventurer sister...

\n<Guild Master>Alright then, you guys register as adventurers! That's the
best course of action. Information comes in easily here.

\n<Guild Master>Besides, adventurers travel from guild to guild as their
base. If you wait here, she might come to you.

\n<Guild Master>How about it? Why don't you work here for now? With that
kind of fighting power, you're not ordinary. You must have
your own circumstances, right?

\n<Guild Master>The folks here don't pry too much. Of course, neither do I.
What do you say?

\n<Louiesham>Thank you very much. (Good, this is pretty much what I
expected.)

\n<Wanzworth>Thank you very much! (Yeah, everything's gone smoothly so
far! Just as planned!)

\n<Guild Master>Then first things first, your names. Write them down on that
paper over there.

\n<Louiesham>... (We can't use our full names. Let's use nicknames or
aliases.)
\n<Wanzworth>... (We should use aliases. You understand, right?)

\n<Louiesham>\n[1]... that's just as it is. Well, whatever. Then I'll be
Louie... there.
\n<Louiesham>\n[1], huh... then I'll go with Louie... there.

\n<Wanzworth>\n[1]? Really? That's okay? Well then, I'll tentatively go
with... Wanz. It's not much of a change.
\n<Wanzworth>\n[1], huh... then I'll just be Wanz.

\n<Guild Master>Aliases are okay too, and you can change them anytime. Well,
that's how laid-back our guild is. Want something to drink?
\n<Louie>Carrot juice, please!
\n<\n[1]>A hot milk, please But not too hot
\n<Wanz>Umm, a hot milk, please But make sure it's not too hot
\n<\n[1]>Carrot juice, please!

\n<Lynx>Ah, the new twins, huh. I'm Lynx. Nice to meet you. The
Master was really off-putting at first, right? That's just
how they are with everyone.

\n<Lynx>But once you get on their good side, they'll treat you well.
It's like that exclusive camaraderie unique to the slums,
you know? Anyway, they're not a bad person.
B
